@Foone It‚Äôs because the Laserdisc player was acting like a computer itself, a #DTE, and not as a #DCE / peripheral.
Connecting any two DTEs (e.g. two PCs) generally required a null modem cable/adapter.
There are reasons the world has mostly moved on from the likes of RS-232 and SCSI!

@Foone What voltage is your RS-232 driver putting out?
